-- Germany’s Leyen Wants Boards to Have 30% Women, Hamburger Says
-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 2012-01-06T06:16:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/germany-s-leyen-wants-boards-to-have-30-women-hamburger-says.html
Ursula von der Leyen,  Germany ’s labor
minister, wants to introduce a mandatory women’s quota of 30
percent for companies’ supervisory boards by 2018,  Hamburger
Abendblatt  reported, citing an interview.  Von der Leyen said Germany is behind Brazil and at the
level of India when it comes to the number of women on boards,
the newspaper reported in the e-mailed preview of an article
that will appear in today’s edition.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ragnhild Kjetland in Frankfurt at 
 rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
